  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean water and new skills for Garadida</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide clean water to 1,176 people of Garadida, plus a school and health post.  No longer will people need to walk dangerous lengths to collect water that often leads to ill health.  Women and men will be trained to maintain and manage the new water system.  They will also receive health and livelihood education, especially in agricultural skills that will lead to improved health and an increased income. A HOPE staff member will live in Garadida for 2 years to embed learning.</narrative>
  </description>
